main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Fostoria, Ohio in August 1966. Five objects were observed for 6-7 minutes.
interesting points: The objects remained virtually motionless and silent.
No further analysis could be performed on the objects.
The observer had no prior experience to compare the objects to.
The objects were described as having a metallic, silvery color.
The objects were estimated to be about 1/3 the size of the observer's view through a match stick held at arm's length.
photographs: no photographs included in the report
